1. instructionAPI
Uses instructionAPI version 1.1.

32bit libraries are in instructionAPI/i386-unknown-linux2.4
- I had to build the 32-bit version of libcommon.so from source,
the distributed copy of libcommon.so couldn't find the symbol
cplus_demangle at link time (linking libbfd didn't seem to help)

64bit libraries are in instructionAPI/x86_64-unknown-linux2.4

to install:
$ cd instructionAPI-1.1/src/dyninst/

Some systems may not already have libelf + libdwarf. If this
is the case you will have to build your own libraries:
    1a. libelf
    $ cd libelf-0.8.9
    $ ./configure
    $ make

    1b. libdwarf
    $ cd dwarf-20100404/libdwarf/
    $ ./configure
    $ make

Then use the following link line:
$ ./configure --with-libelf-incdir=${PEBIL_ROOT}/external/libelf-0.8.9/lib --with-libelf-libdir=${PEBIL_ROOT}/external/libelf-0.8.9/lib --with-libdwarf-incdir=${PEBIL_ROOT}/external/dwarf-20100404/libdwarf/ --with-libdwarf-libdir=${PEBIL_ROOT}/external/dwarf-20100404/libdwarf/ --prefix=${PEBIL_ROOT}/external/instructionAPI-1.1

If your system already has libelf + libdwarf, use this config line:
$ ./configure --prefix=${PEBIL_ROOT}/external

Then continue with the normal build stuff...
$ make
$ make install

2. udis86

to install:
$ cd udis86-1.7
$ ./configure --prefix=${PWD}/external
$ make
$ make install
